                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1683">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.51/700.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Minister of Nicaragua</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 19, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Minister</hi>: With reference to the
                    Department’s note to you of October 14, 1914, in which reference was made to a
                    cable addressed to you by the Minister of Foreign Affairs of Nicaragua,
                    requesting a loan of $50,000, I have the honor to inform you that a reply has
                    been received from Brown Brothers &amp; Company and Seligman &amp; Company, in
                    which they express their regret at not being able to comply with the request for
                    this additional loan.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
